body:
Latest Git version. SystemVerilog-2023 standard (I did not check if this is different in older versions).

The next SystemVErilog code:

```SystemVerilog
module sscanf_tb #(
  parameter int unsigned XLEN = 32
);

  string pkt;
  int unsigned idx;
  logic [XLEN-1:0] val;
  int code;

  initial begin
    // register index and value
    string pkt = "P20=4cff0000";
    code = $sscanf(pkt, "P%h=%8h", idx, val);
    $display("DEBUG: code=%0d pkt='P%0h=%08h'", code, idx, val);
  end

endmodule: sscanf_tb
```

Gives a  runtime error (not exactly from this example):

```
%Error: /usr/local/share/verilator/include/verilated.cpp:1456: Unknown _vl_vsscanf code: 8
```

I noticed the standard also specifies an _"optional assignment suppression character `*`"_, which might also not be supported.

I could create a few regression testcases (checked against simulators on EDAplayground) and a pull request, if it would help.

